  speciesName: Ryufuku
  speciesDesc: 'Ryufuku is found in the seas of Japan. The Ryufuku is a sea serpent
    shaped dragon that floats through the environment. Ryufuku also may be holding
    a mystical jewel, in ancient times they used this to control the tides. Now,
    the jewel is used as a mystical object that the dragon likes to play with or
    perhaps used in granting luck to others. Wishing and meditating to this dragon
    may bring you luck in the near future. '
